description: From Middle English bemenen, equivalent to be- +‎ mean (“to signify”). Compare Middle High German bemeinen (“to mean”).

verbs.description: bemean (third-person singular simple present bemeans, present participle bemeaning, simple past and past participle bemeant)

description: From be- +‎ mean (“base, lowly”), from Middle English mene, aphetic variation of Middle English imene (“average, lowly, mean”), from Old English ġemǣne (“mean, common, average”). More at mean.

verbs.description: bemean (third-person singular simple present bemeans, present participle bemeaning, simple past and past participle bemeaned)

entries.meaning: To make mean or base, demean.
